The paper discusses the development of a deep learning model for automatic detection of diagnostic images in brain tumor surgery using confocal laser endomicroscopy (CLE). This involves image analysis and classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep learning models for this task also suggests the likelihood of the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of histological features for localization, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
